author: joymarilie
desc: @joymarilie All adults are not worthy of compliance, or obedience. Teaching my child to evaluate adult behavior is a skill that will hopefully prevent her from being a victim. Most children are abused by trusted adults. Teaching stranger danger just won’t cut it. All adults, including me and others close to her, are allowed to be challenged when their behavior is suspect or disrespectful. You know why this doesn’t bother me? Because I have a mutually respectful relationship with my child and expect all adults who interact with her to follow suit. This would only bother you if you plan on disrespecting kids. I have a cooperative, respectful critical thinker. I’m good with those qualities over obedience.  #blackparenting #consciousparenting #gentleparenting #blackmotherhood #blackmomsbelike #thejacksoncrew #positiveparenting  #respectfulparenting #consciousteacher #blackmoms  #parentingtips

author: brunchwithbabs
desc: Babs’ Way to Hold Family Meetings 📝 Pick a day and time to have your meeting each week and stick to it.  Mr Babs and I meet Sundays at 5:00pm.  Stay consistent. And in no time, you will feel better and more like a team!  Here is Babs’ way to hold a family meeting: 📝 1)  To Do Lists and Calendars.  Review the To Do List from the week before and go over the To Do List (or Honey Do List) for the week ahead.  Go over calendars together, shared and personal.   📝2)  Family Issues.  Discuss how each family member is doing and any outstanding issues or family plans that need to be made.  This is also a great time for holiday and travel planning.   📝3)  Finance and Budget.  Review where you stand and plan ahead for expenses.   Go Team!  XO Babs #familymeeting #householditems #marriagetips
